docs.abstract: President Trump said there was a “very, very good chance” of a trade deal with China being reached when he meets with the Chinese president in March.
docs.snippet: President Trump said there was a “very, very good chance” of a trade deal with China being reached when he meets with the Chinese president in March.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump said the United States and China were moving closer toward a trade agreement and suggested that the fate of Huawei, the Chinese telecom giant facing criminal charges along with its chief financial officer, could be resolved as part of a final trade deal with Beijing.

headline.main: U.S. and China Extend Talks, but Final Deal Remains Elusive
headline.print_headline: U.S. Inches Toward Pact With China On Trade

byline.original: By Ana Swanson and Alan Rappeport

docs.abstract: The potential bans of Huawei technology is overshadowing the mobile phone industry’s biggest annual event in Barcelona.
docs.snippet: The potential bans of Huawei technology is overshadowing the mobile phone industry’s biggest annual event in Barcelona.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Wireless carriers have for years said the next generation network, known as 5G, will provide not only hyper-fast mobile phone speeds, but breakthroughs for data-heavy technologies like autonomous vehicles, robotics and artificial intelligence.

headline.main: Huawei’s Plight Hangs Over Wireless Industry Showcase
headline.print_headline: Huawei’s Plight Hangs  Over Wireless Showcase

docs.abstract: Robert Lighthizer, the United States trade representative, must defend a trade pact that is shaping up to be less ambitious than he might once have hoped.
docs.snippet: Robert Lighthizer, the United States trade representative, must defend a trade pact that is shaping up to be less ambitious than he might once have hoped.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump has signaled that he is moving toward peace with China in a trade standoff that has rattled markets and businesses globally. But as he backs off his threat to impose higher tariffs, the president’s relationship with his own trade negotiator is now showing signs of strain.

headline.main: Trump Undermines Top Trade Adviser as He Pushes for China Deal
headline.print_headline: President Puts Trade Adviser In Tough Spot

docs.abstract: Former business partners involved in the venerable queer publication are locked in a lengthy battle. A writers union has threatened a lawsuit.
docs.snippet: Former business partners involved in the venerable queer publication are locked in a lengthy battle. A writers union has threatened a lawsuit.
docs.lead_paragraph: With a new editor in chief, a new staff and a new look, the February issue of Out magazine represented a fresh start for the groundbreaking queer publication. Two young Hollywood stars, Hari Nef and Tommy Dorfman, made for lovely cover subjects. Splashy ads from Louis Vuitton, Cadillac and Gucci seemed like good omens for a prosperous future.

headline.main: Out Magazine’s Fresh Start Overshadowed by a Bitter Money Dispute
headline.print_headline: Out Magazine’s Fresh Start Is Troubled by Pay Dispute

docs.abstract: In a move certain to upset American and European Union leaders, Italy appears poised to cooperate in an infrastructure initiative meant to advance China’s global interests and influence.
docs.snippet: In a move certain to upset American and European Union leaders, Italy appears poised to cooperate in an infrastructure initiative meant to advance China’s global interests and influence.
docs.lead_paragraph: ROME — In a move certain to cause consternation among American officials and leaders of the European Union, Italy appears poised to help China extend its vast global infrastructure push deeper into Western Europe, part of Beijing’s sweeping plan to advance its economic interests and influence around the world.

headline.main: Italy May Split With Allies and Open Its Ports to China’s Building Push
headline.print_headline: Italy May Cross Allies and Open Up to China’s Building Push

byline.original: By Jason Horowitz and Jack Ewing

docs.abstract: The clash has consequences beyond New York, going to the heart of a national debate likely to dominate the 2020 election: What is the best way to spread prosperity?
docs.snippet: The clash has consequences beyond New York, going to the heart of a national debate likely to dominate the 2020 election: What is the best way to spread prosperity?
docs.lead_paragraph: The political opposition that prompted Amazon to walk away from building a corporate headquarters in New York City featured a touchstone of the progressives’ economic agenda: ending tax policies that unfairly reward and pamper the wealthy.

headline.main: In Amazon Fight, Progressives Showed What They Want: A New Economic Agenda
headline.print_headline: Amazon’s Exit Reignites a Debate Over Growth

docs.abstract: Hoping to beat Uber to the market, Lyft plans to talk up its offering to investors, known as the roadshow, in mid-March and go public in early April.
docs.snippet: Hoping to beat Uber to the market, Lyft plans to talk up its offering to investors, known as the roadshow, in mid-March and go public in early April.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — In a rush to beat its rival Uber to the public market, Lyft is preparing to start trading in early April, according to two people familiar with the company’s plans.

headline.main: Lyft Sets Crucial Date in Race to I.P.O.
headline.print_headline: Lyft Sets Roadshow Date In the Race to Go Public

byline.original: By Mike Isaac and Kate Conger

docs.abstract: Virgin Hyperloop One is testing a system that would put passengers in pods hurtling through vacuum tubes. Other companies are moving ahead with similar plans.
docs.snippet: Virgin Hyperloop One is testing a system that would put passengers in pods hurtling through vacuum tubes. Other companies are moving ahead with similar plans.
docs.lead_paragraph: MOAPA, Nev. — California just decided to sharply scale back its plans for a high-speed rail artery meant to transform travel up and down the state. But in the desert outside Las Vegas, the transportation ambitions still seem limitless.

headline.main: A Real Tube Carrying Dreams of 600-M.P.H. Transit
headline.print_headline: 600 M.P.H.: No Wings, No Wheels, Just a Tube

docs.abstract: Michael Calvey, founder of one of the biggest and oldest investment firms in Russia, was detained on Friday along with five other.
docs.snippet: Michael Calvey, founder of one of the biggest and oldest investment firms in Russia, was detained on Friday along with five other.
docs.lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — The American founder of one of the oldest and largest Russia-focused private equity firms was detained on fraud charges in Moscow on Friday in a case that jolted the country’s business community.

headline.main: U.S. Private Equity Investor Detained in Moscow on Fraud Charges
headline.print_headline: U.S. Investor Is Charged With Fraud In Russia

docs.abstract: Gaby Dunn, Chanel Reynolds and Vicki Robin were born decades apart. But their books about money have a common thread: Talk about it way, way more often.
docs.snippet: Gaby Dunn, Chanel Reynolds and Vicki Robin were born decades apart. But their books about money have a common thread: Talk about it way, way more often.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Personal finance professionals live too often in the realm of tools and tactics, optimization and automation. All too frequently, their advice — our advice — is utterly bloodless.

headline.main: The Power of Raw, Honest Stories About Money
headline.print_headline: The Power of Talking  Honestly About Money
